div1.p:
Q. Did you plan the robbery - A. No;
Thomas Smithers
planned it. I do not know where he is. When they came up two glasses were taken from the carriage. I cut off one string and Smithers the other. I took them out of the premises, and the prisoner carried them away. I went with him; we were both stopped at two o'clock; he had the glasses; I got away as soon as they laid hold of him.
